# Slash workflow

Context: **`AGENTS.md`**, **`core/project-conventions.mdc`** (immutable graph, user-goals, data-model).

**Invoke:** `/` in chat → pick command or skill. **Canonical prose** lives in **`.cursor/commands/*.md`**; repeatable runners in **`.cursor/skills/*/SKILL.md`**. Shared task-file rules: **`workpkg-hygiene.mdc`**.

| Intent | Slash |
| --- | --- |
| New multi-step initiative, fuzzy goals | `/define-project` |
| Goals clear → task files | `/define-tasks` |
| ShaderToy gap analysis | `/analyze-shadertoy` |
| Execute one tracked task | `/implement-task` (attach `_OVERVIEW` + task markdown) |
| CI / Pages green | `/prepare-commit` (`npm run verify:pages`) |
| Post-project QA pass | `/review-project` |
| Architecture findings → maybe WPs | `/review-architecture` |
| Structured pass on one shader node (impl + UX) | `/review-node` |
| Performance findings → maybe WPs | `/review-performance` |
| Capture investigated bug | `/write-bug` |
| Close loop on `docs/bug/` report | `/review-bug` |
| Prune / relocate stale `docs/`; refresh `docs/architecture/` vs code | `/cleanup-docs` |
| Clean up shipped `docs/implementation/` packages | See `docs-implementation-done-cleanup.mdc` |
| Audit Cursor agent config itself | `/review-agent-tooling` |
| Audit `$effect` usage vs Svelte 5 guidance | `/audit-svelte-effects` |

After big structural changes: consider new/updated **`docs/`** or **`.cursor/rules/`** entries — propose separately, don’t fold into unrelated implementation PRs unless required.
